 "base_path": "/hmrc-internal-manuals/business-income-manual/bim51510",
 "body": "<p>S25 Income Tax (Trading and Other Income) Act 2005, S46 Corporation Tax Act 2009</p>\n\n<p>For tax purposes, accounts prepared according to generally accepted accounting practice are the starting point for calculating trade profits.</p>\n\n<p>Such accounts are therefore also the starting point for income recognition for tax purposes, subject to any over-riding statutory or case law principle (see <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/hmrc-internal-manuals/business-income-manual/bim30510\">BIM30510</a>).</p>\n\n<p>The guidance on income recognition is arranged as follows</p>\n",
